좋은 아침, 우리 엄마.

이번주 내가 성천교회 갈까요? 그 교수님이 많이 주시기에 자주 가도 된 것 같아요.

우리 엄마 아마 아들이 못되서 자기에게 업신여김을 초래하는 것 같아요.

그래서 한 마디 드릴게요.

한마디는: 그들이 엄마의 음식이나 아들을 업신여기는 것은 음식이 맛없다는 것도 아니고 아들이 못된 것도 아니라 그저 엄마를 업신여기는 것일뿐이라는 말이에요.

우리 엄마 만든 것은 거기서 맛있어도 혐오를 당해요. 내가 왜 화내요? 그저 내가 그들이 나를 업신여기는 것을 알기 때문에요. 만약에 나와 엄마는 한 명이라도 존경받으면 그들이 그렇게 할 수 없어요. 이렇게 보면 진짜로 아들이 못되서 엄마에게 업신여김을 초래하는 것은 맞는 것이에요. 아들이 못되서 거기서 엄마에게 존경을 초래하지 못해서 미안해요.





주제: 어제 심야 1시 까지 예배드렸다. 

우리 엄마, 잘 지내셨어요. 

어제 1시 까지 진행하던 송구영신 예배 때문에 늦게 잤으니 오늘 10시까지 잤어요. 그리고 밥 두끼나 먹었어요. 

제가 여기에 매일 매일 머리 위에 비행기 소리를 들어요. 제가 비행기 소리를 들을때 "엄마가 이 안에 있냐"는 생각이 생겨요. 엄마께서 어느 비행기에 타고 있으면 좋겠어요. 
어쩔수 없이 혼자서 잘 살아야 돼요. 

우리 원장목사님이 다시 중국 선교를 시작한다고 선포했어요. 지금 전문적인 통역이 오면 돼요. 
싸고 그의 말을 듣고 순종하는 통역이 엄마밖에 그분이 찾기 어려워요. 그가 이선생님을 쓰려고 하지만 엄마밖에 그를 참을 수 있는 자는 별로 없어요. 

저는 한국어 서툴러요. 아무튼 하나님께 감사해요. 촌닭이에다가 머리가 둔한 내가 이 정도 하더라도 이미 하나님께서 주신 큰 은혜이라고 생각해요. 
하나님이 선하셔서 하나님께 감사해요. 

그의 일을 진행하기 위해 중국에서도 사람이 있어야 돼요. 그의 생각대로 쉽게 될 수 없어요. 
하지만 하나님이 허락하시면 문제가 있어도 잘 해결할 수 있을거에요. 

하나님이 그의 놀로우신 은혜로 그의 일을 성취하시길 원해요. 





주제: 교회 목사와 애터미 성도의 소리 없는 싸움. 

우리 엄마, 잘 지내셨어요? 



오늘 날씨가 덜 추웠어요. 아마 제일 추운 시절이 끝났어나 봐요. 



오늘 수요 예배 마친 후, 임체월 권사님이 내게 한 봉지를 주셨어요. 샌드위치 두개가 있어 목사님이랑 같이 먹어라고 했어요. 이 권사님이 지난 주 라면 한 상자를 주셨어요. 



하지만 이상한 점은 목사님이 바로 옆에 계신 것이에요. 그 둘 사이 않 좋냐고 생각해요. 

그 다음에 목사님이 기분이 나쁜 표정하고 소리로 저녁을 먹었다고 하셨어요. 우리 목사님이 진짜로 사람을 기분 나쁘게 하는 분인 것 같아요. 제가 두개를 다 가져가고 싶지만 욕심을 내면 안된다고 생각해서 한개 드렸어요. 아무튼 목사님이 받았어요. 



돌아온 후, 생각해 보니까, 왜 목사님이 그의 성도 사이가 이렇게 안 좋아요? 그리고 그 권사님이 주신 라면이 생각났어요. 

그 권사님이 애터미 성도이에요. 



우리 엄마 말씀하신 어떤 사람이 자기에게 좋게 해주고 최후에 애터미를 소개했다는 얘기가 생각났어요. 아, 그렇군요. 

이 교회의 목사님을 얻으면 그 안에 있는 모든 성도들을 얻을 수 있다는 것을 다들 알아요. 그리고 목사님도 알아요. 그래서 둘이 사이 나쁘게 된 것 같아요. 



아무튼 제가 옆에 보니까 재미있어요. 아무래도 돈이 없는 나를 이끌어갈 사람이 없어요. 공짜로 재미있는 것을 볼 수 있어요. 

돈이 없는 것은 하나님이 주신 신비한 은혜라는 것을 한번더 깨닫게 되었어요. 하나님이 있어서 제가 행복해요. 그리고 다른 사람이 좋지 않는 뜻을 이루기 위해 나를 이용하지만 하나님이 그 좋지 않는 뜻을 막아주고 그의 좋은 뜻대로 내게 음식물을 주셨어요. 



돈이 없는 은혜로 남의 나쁜 뜻을 막아 주신 하나님께 감사해요. 

나중의 인생도 하나님이 계속계속 그의 지혜의 은혜를 내게 주시길 원해요. 감사를 은혜로우신 하나님께 드립니다. 아멘. 





주제: 언제 학교에 가서 비자 연장하면 좋냐? 

우리 엄마, 날씨가 따뜻해졌어요? 겨울에 진짜로 추워요. 그리고 여름에 더워요. 인생은 진짜로 어려워요. 

학교의 소식대로 하면 제가 학교 교무처에 가서 각종 증명서를 받아야 돼요. 그럼 제가 학교에 언제 갈까요? 

제가 이번 기회로 중국에 돌아가고 싶지만 도대체 하나님이 이 일을 순조롭게 하지 않으셨어요. 
그래서 나귀에게 막힌 선지자처럼 자기 마음대로 하지 말고 하나님이 주신 길로 가겠어요. 

제가 성천 교회에 와서 교회생활 하면서 엄마를 기다리는 것은 절반이나 이루었어요. 아무튼 하나님께 감사해요. 
떠나가야 하면 언제 목사님께 말씀드릴까요? 

그리고 목사님이 위쳇으로 찍은 동영상을 보낸 방식으로 중국 선교를 재개하고 싶어나 봐요. 
어제 목사님이 개학 날짜를 물어볼 때 자기를 돕기 위해 나를 여기에 두고 싶지만 제가 "대부분 교수님이 인터넷으로 수업하지만 어떤 교수님이 대면으로 수업한다"고 대답했어요. 

이일성 선생님의 어머니께서 내게 물만두하고 皮冻하고 맛있는 반찬을 주시기 때문에 제가 이선생님을 위해 많이 기도했어요. 
엄마께서 혼자 이런 일을 하기에 조금 어려울 것 같아서 이 선생님이 돌아와서 이 일을 도울 수 있으면 좋겠어요. 

아무튼 하나님의 일이 반드시 이루어질 것입니다. 하나님의 영이 우리에게 임하시고 그를 위해 살아가게 하시기를 원합니다. 





주제: 제 열심이 주인의 열심보다 더 많고 지금 회개하겠다. 

우리 엄마, 잘 지내셨어요? 



우리 오늘 눈이 왔어요. 엄마 쪽에 눈이 있어요? 



오늘 아들이 진짜로 많은 일을 겪었어요. 그리고 많이 생각하게 되었어요. 



아침 부터 정욕의 꿈을 꿨어요. 그 나쁜 영향은 지금도 남아 있어요. 



오전에 제가 목사님의 사무실에 가서 영상 올리는 것을 했어요. 전화번호 때문에 많은 어려움을 당했어요. 마지막에 성공했어요. 하지만 목사님에게 방해가 되었어요. 



점심때 사모님, 목사님, 어떤 집사님하고 같이 장어를 먹었어요. 식탁에서 목사님이 내게 아르바이트를 해라고 권장했어요. 그분이 내가 일이 없어서 그래서 매일 그를 찾았다고 생각하는 것 같아요. 

그의 아르바이트하는 학생이 많아요. 하지만 그가 칭찬하냐요? 심지어 이야기조차도 안 해요. 하지만 내가 영어 토픽 시험을 신청할 때 그분이 하신 말씀이 생각났어요. 내가 공부할 시간이 있으면 그분이 불만하는 것 같아요. 영어 뿐만 아니라 심지어 그의 모국어 인 한국어에 대해서도 그가 불만밖에 없어요. 제주도에 있었을때 그의 말씀은 여기에 있는데에 하신 말씀과 똑같아요. 그의 학생이 공부하면 그가 불만해요. 그리고 그의 학생이 그의 말씀따라 아르바이트 하면 그분이 더 불만해요. 



제가 그의 일을 위해 열심히 일하고 있지만 그분이 그의 일을 쉽게 생각해서 제가 매일 할 일 없이 그저 그를 방해하다는 것을 알아요. 그럼 제가 왜 더 이상 그의 일을 위해 열심히 해요? 제가 지금 포기할게요. 그 서버도 중지할게요. 돈을 괜히 낭비해요. 

제가 당장 학교에 돌아가고 싶지만 시험장소는 서울로 선택해서 어쩔수 없어요. 그리고 제가 이것을 하나님의 은혜라고 생각해요. 왜냐하면 제가 어쩔수 없어요. 



점심을 하고 돌아와서 사모님이 나와 많이 이야기 했어요. 목사님의 강단밖에 생활에 대해, 그리고 백루에 대해 많이 불만했어요. 

하나님이 세우신 분이라서 사모님이 그의 남편을 주님으로 생각해요. 하지만 그분이 여전히 완벽하지 않는 인간이라서 불만도 있어요. 아무튼 지나왔어요. 

인간을 의지하는 것은 고통밖에 없다, 하지만 하나님이 선하신 분이라서 하나님이 있으면 된다고 했어요. 



이야기 끝난 후 제가 자기 방에 돌아와서 듣고 겪고 생각하는 것을 적었어요. 그리고 엄마한테 편지를 써요. 그리고 서버를 중지했어요. 지금 방문하지 못하게 되었어요. 



제가 이제 과도한 열심을 하지 않고 자기 일을 하겠습니다. 

열심히 시험을 준비하겠습니다. 그리고 支付宝도 삭제하겠습니다. 더 이상 이런 일을 하지 않겠습니다. 



제가 많약에 여기에 시험을 신청을 하지 않았으면 떠나갈 것이에요. 하나님이 선하신 뜻이 어떤 것인지 제가 바라보고 기다리겠습니다. 

그리고요, 우리 하나님이 자기 열심을 가지고 일하는 사람을 제일 싫어하시 분인 것 같아요. 제가 진짜로 잘못했어요. 



아무튼 하나님이 있어서 모든 것이 다 좋아요. 이것이 저것이 좋다는 것은 아니에요. 우리 하나님이 좋으신 분이세요. 

좋으셔서 우리를 구원하신 하나님께 감사해요. 그분이 우리를 완전하게 하신 날이 이르기를 원해요. 모든 영광이 그분께 있습니다. 아멘. 









Revised Version----------------------------------

Chapter 6, Nanjing, the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom movement and the beginning of modern China. 

The dream of those missionaries who came into China mainland, is to preach the Gospel around the whole China. But this dream was explained in a wrong way and led to revolution in China and killed many people, the man who raised the revolution was HongXiuquan, and his explanation of the kingdom of heaven in the earth was his "the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom". 

HongXiuquan lost in an exam in 1836, and he got the book of "QuanShiLiangYan" from a missionary, but he didn't care about this at first. After he lost again and again in the imperial examinations, he had no way but back to his hometown. He sickened severely in his hometown for 40 days, and in that period he thought of the book which he had gotten, he saw something is alike with the content of this book in his dream, he understood something by himself and became a christian. He had studied a little doctrine of Christianity from a pastor, but did not understand it wholly, thus he designed the idea of "the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom" by his experience and his lust. 

HongXiuquan called the Father "Heavenly Father'' and called Jesus as the firstborn of God, furthermore he called himself a brother of Jesus Christ. He used the complaint of people and built "the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom" and allied with another community called "Heaven and Earth Community". Thus he started from Southwest China and conquered many places in China. Finally he conquered Nanjing in March, 1853 and killed 30,000 soldiers of the Qing dynasty. He changed the name of Nanjing to "Tianjin" which means "the city of heaven", started his "the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom", the fulfillment in the earth of the kingdom of heaven written in the Bible, and he marched toward Beijing. 

HongXiuquan couldn't conquer Beijing and was defeated by the armies of the Qing dynasty. He tried to ask help from the pastor who has had taught him in 1860, but because he called himself as the brother of Jesus and let the pastor admit this, the pastor left him, thus he suicide with poison, and Nanjing was conquered in July, 1864, that's means the ending of "the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom" within 15 years. 

Shunwen, Shun Zhong shan was a different figure with HongXiuquan, he overthrew the old China and prepared the modern China, also he was a christian. Shunwen was born in 1866, as a youngest son of a poor peasant family, with the help of his oldest brother, he lived in China until he was 12 years old and afterward he went to the place Hawaii where his oldest brother lived. He met the western culture in Hawaii and started to understand the world. He entered Iolani College in 1879, and grew from a country boy to be a man who has global views. After he graduated from above one college, he entered Oahu College, he was asked to become a christian in this school, but was prevented by his oldest brother who believes in Confucianism. So he returned to China in 1883, and found that China is so different from Hawaii where he had lived. 

Sunwen was baptized and became a christian in November, 1883 with his friends by pastor Charles Hager. He entered The Central School in April 1884, most of his friends in the revolution movements were Christian. He tried to save the world as a physician, and opened his pharmacy in Macau, 1893, but he decided to concentrate on revolution with his friends in 1895. Finally he combined the power in China and out of China and started the revolution and built the "Republic of China" as the first president. His dream is to be a man like Moses who released Israel from Egypt, or Jesus who saved humans from the sins. He thought that his revolution is the fire but his religion is the oil which makes the fire blaze. He glorified God by his revolution, he said that the success of revolution relies on the grace of God. He died in 1925, and was buried in Nanjing, 1929. He is called the "Founding Father" by all Chinese. 

The foundation of modern China was built by Sunwen, but the foundation of modern China's church was built by DingGuanxun. DingGuanxun was born in 1915, a christian family of Shanghai, his grandfather was a pastor of Anglican and his mother was a faithful christian. As a tradition of the church, he was baptized when he was just 4 months, and he attended church to worship every week. Thus he received christian education from his childhood. When he went to St. John's College, his major was civil engineering, and his father hoped him to become an excellent engineer. However he transferred to Arts to study English and Theology after 1 year, and became a pastor after he graduated in 1942. He was elected as the dean of Nanjing Concord Theological Seminary in 1952 when he was 37 years old, afterward he decided to the cultivation of a pastor who took care of religion and nation both. He became a bishop of Anglican in 1955. He took part in the building of Amity Foundation as a main role. In 1986, The United Bible Societies and The Amity Printing Company was built and became the main printing office in China to print all current versions of the Bible. He died in 2012, Nanjing, at 98. 

A special American woman who had lived in China and written the book "Earth" about Chinese life was Pearl Sydenstricker Buck. She was a writer, a humanist, a feminist, and a missionary of Presbyterian. She entered China when she was 3 months old with his missionary parents, and lived in ZhenJiang for 18 years. She thought Chinese is her first language. Her life in HuaBei was the material of her works including "Earth". 

In the building process of modern China, which is called "People's Republic of China", there are many christian as the main roles, such as ShunWen, the Founding Father of modern China. From history, we can easily find out that the Christianity changed the whole world, regardless of ancient or modern world. The power of God's word affects the world in a hidden way we can hardly get it, but through history we can easily find it out. The word of God, contained in the religion called Christianity, has enormous power. 

On the national level, God's word has such power, let alone the individual level. In our life, the word of God seems useless or powerless, just a word without any power, however the word of God affects us and changes us by a secretive method. He changed our mind, changed our life, and even changed the whole world. The word of God, incarnated in the flesh of humans, he is Jesus. The Christianity, which was created by Jesus and his disciples, influenced the earth. No matter in ancient China or modern China, the religion of Christianity will affect and change the nation. Although it seems there are many persecutions in China mainland, we believe that God's will be done, as in heaven, so on earth. The name of God be kept holy. 

Revised Version----------------------------------




Chapter 6, Nanjing, the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom movement and the beginning of modern China. 

The dream of those missionaries who came into China mainland, is to preach the Gospel around the whole China. But this dream be explained by a wrong way and lead to revolution in China and killed many people, the man risen the revolution was HongXiuquan, and his explanation of the kingdom of heaven in the earth was his "the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom". 

HongXiuquan lost in an exam in 1836, and he got the book of "QuanShiLiangYan" from a missionary, but he didn't care of this at first. After he lost again and again in the exam of imperial examinations, he had no way but back to his hometown. He sicked severely in his hometown for 40 days, and in that period he thought of the book which he had gotten, he saw something is alike with the content of this book in his dream, he understand something by himself and became a christian. He has had studied a little doctrine of Christianity from a pastor, but did not understand it wholly, thus he designed the idea of "the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom" by his experience and his lust. 

HongXiuquan called the Father "Heavenly Father" and called Jesus as the firstborn of God, further more he called himself a brother of Jesus Christ. He use the complaint of people and built "the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom" and allied with another community called "Heaven and Earth Community". Thus he started from the Southwest China and conquered many place of China. Finally he conquered Nanjing in March, 1853 and killed 30,000 soldiers of the Qing dynasty. He changed the name of Nanjing to "Tianjing" which means "the city of heaven", started his "the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom", the fulfillment in the earth of the kingdom of heaven written in Bible, and he marched toward Beijing. 

HongXiuquan couldn't conquer Beijing and defeated by the armies of the Qing dynasty. He tried to ask help from the pastor who has had taught him in 1860, but because he called himself as the brother of Jesus and let the pastor admit this, the pastor left him, thus he suicide with poison, and Nanjing was conquered in July, 1864, that's means the ending of "the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom" within 15 years. 

Shunwen, ShunZhongsan was a different figure with HongXiuquan, he overthrew the old China and prepared the modern China, also he was a christian. Shunwen was born in 1866, as a youngest son of a poor peasant family, with the help of his oldest brother, he lived in China until he was 12 years old and afterward he went to the place Hawaii where his oldest brother lived. He met the western culture in Hawaii and started to understand the world. He entered Iolani College in 1879, and grew from a country boy to be a man who has global views. After he graduated from above one college, he entered into Oahu College, he was asked to become a christian in this school, but be prevented by his oldest brother who believes in Confucianism. Thus he backed to China in 1883, and found that China is so different with Hawaii where he has had lived. 

Sunwen was baptized and became a christian in November, 1883 with his friends by pastor Charles Hager. He entered into The Central School in April 1884, most of his friends in the revolution movements were Christian. He tried to save the world as a physician, and opened his pharmacy in Macao, 1893, but he decided to concentrate on revolution with his friends in 1895. Finally he combined the power in China and out of China and started the revolution and built the "Republic of China" as the first president. His dream is to be a man like Moses who released Israel from Egypt, or Jesus who saved human from the sins. He thought that his revolution is the fire but the his religion is the oil which makes the fire blaze. He glorified God by his revolution, he said that the success of revolution rely on the grace of God. He died in 1925, and was buried in Nanjing, 1929. He is called the "Founding Father" by all Chinese. 

The foundation of modern China was built by Sunwen, but the foundation of modern China's church was built by DingGuanxun. DingGuanxun was born in 1915, a christian family of Shanghai, his grandfather was a pastor of Anglican and his mother was a faithful christian. As a tradition of church, he was baptized when he was just 4 months, and he attend church to worship every week. Thus he received christian education from his childhood. When he went to St. John's College, his major was civil engineering, and his father hoped him to become an excellent engineer. However he transferred to Arts to study English and Theology after 1 year, and became a pastor after he graduate in 1942. He was elected as the dean of Nanjing Concord Theological Seminary in 1952 when he was 37 years old, afterward he decided to the cultivation of a pastor who take care of religion and nation both. He became a bishop of Anglican in 1955. He partook in the building of Amity Foundation as a main role. In 1986, The United Bible Societies and The Amity Printing Company was built and became the main printing office in China to print all current versions of the Bible. He died in 2012, Nanjing, at his 98. 

A special American woman who has had lived in China and written the book "Earth" about Chinese life was Pearl Sydenstricker Buck. She was a writer, a humanist, a feminist, and a missionary of Presbyterian. She entered into China when she was 3 months with his missionary parents, and lived in ZhenJiang for 18 years. She thought Chinese is her first language. Her life in HuaBei was the material of her works including "Earth". 

In the building process of modern China, which called "People's Republic of China", there are many christian as the main roles, such as ShunWen, the Founding Father of modern China. From the history, we can easily find out that the Christianity changed the whole world, regardless of ancient or modern world. The power of God's word affect the world in a hidden way we can hardly get it, but through the history we can easily find out it. The word of God, contained in the religion called Christianity, has enormous power. 

In the national level, God's word has such power, let alone the individual level. In our life, the word of God seems useless or powerless, just a word without any power, however the word of God affect us and change us by a secretive method. He changed our mind, changed our life, and even changed the whole world. The word of God, incarnated in the flesh of human, he is Jesus. The Christianity which created by Jesus and his disciples, influenced the earth. No matter in ancient China or modern China, the religion of Christianity will affect and change the nation. Although it seems there are many persecution in China mainland, we believe that God's will be done, as in heaven, so on earth. The name of God be kept holy. 



